So we think we may have found the problem.

In xxx.features.ui.internal.AddRemoveFeaturesWizard, we needed to run the 
feature install delegates inside the workspace runnable context instead of the 
wizard runnable context to ensure that the AVOID_UPDATE flag is respected and 
resource change events aren't fired.

Unfortunately, the only way we could see to do that is to run inside a 
ProgressMonitorDialog.  See https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?
id=109202  So now we've got the weird effect of a modal dialog popping up 
after you hit the finish button on the wizard.

If you guys know of a workaround or better way to do this, please let us 
know.  Below is the updated AddRemoveFeaturesWizard.performFinish() method:

    public boolean performFinish() 
    {
        for( int i = 0; i < this.featurePages.length; i++ )
        {
            final FeaturePages fp = this.featurePages[ i ];

            for( int j = 0; j < fp.pages.length; j++ )
            {
                fp.pages[ j ].transferStateToConfig();
            }
        }

        // We'll wrap the actuall installs in a WorkspaceModifyOperation
        // so we'll have a lock on the workspace when the project is being 
        // createed. Run each of the install delegates before releasing that
        // lock
        final WorkspaceModifyOperation op = new WorkspaceModifyOperation() 
        {
            protected void execute( final IProgressMonitor monitor ) throws 
CoreException 
            {
                // TODO: Description an I18N
                monitor.beginTask( "", actions.size() );

                try
                {
                    performFinish( monitor );
                }
                finally
                {
                    monitor.done();
                }
            }
        };

        // We'll need to put everything in a workspace runnable, too, 
        // because we'll want to show a progress dialog as we're installing
        // the features. The only purpose of the workspace runnable is
        // to execute the WorkspaceModifyOperation. Since a 
WorkspaceModifyOperation
        // executes inline, we sill will have created only one new thread
        final IWorkspaceRunnable wr = new IWorkspaceRunnable()
        {
            public void run(IProgressMonitor monitor) throws CoreException
            {
                try
                {
                    op.run(monitor);
                }
                catch(InterruptedException ie)
                {
                    IStatus status = new Status(IStatus.ERROR,
                                                FeaturesUiPlugin.PLUGIN_ID,
                                                IStatus.OK,
                                                ie.getLocalizedMessage(),
                                                ie);
                    throw new CoreException(status);
                }
                catch(InvocationTargetException ite)
                {
                    IStatus status = new Status(IStatus.ERROR,
                                                FeaturesUiPlugin.PLUGIN_ID,
                                                IStatus.OK,
                                                ite.getLocalizedMessage(),
                                                ite);
                    throw new CoreException(status);
                }
            }
        };

        // Finally, we can't run the workspace runnable in the wizard's modal
        // context because the wizard's modal context does not batch the 
        // resource events. We need to run in the workspace's modal context
        // which will allow us to pass in the AVOID_UPDATE flags that will
        // allow all of the features to be installed before we kick of resource
        // events that can cause concurrent WebArtifactEdit modifactions 
        Shell activeShell = getContainer().getShell();
        ProgressMonitorDialog progressDialog = new ProgressMonitorDialog
(activeShell)
        {
            // Overriding the ProgressDialog's run method allows us to swap the
            // modal context for the workspace modal context
            public void run(boolean fork, 
                            boolean cancelable,
                            IRunnableWithProgress runnable)
                    throws InvocationTargetException, InterruptedException
            {
                // TODO: should we honor the cancelable parameter?
                setCancelable(false);
                try
                {
                    aboutToRun();
                    IWorkspace workspace = ResourcesPlugin.getWorkspace();
                    workspace.run(wr, 
                                  workspace.getRoot(), 
                                  IWorkspace.AVOID_UPDATE, 
                                  getProgressMonitor());
                }
                catch(CoreException ce)
                {
                    throw new InvocationTargetException(ce);
                }
                finally
                {
                    finishedRun();
                }
            }
        };

        try
        {
            progressDialog.run(true, true, op);
        }
        catch( InterruptedException e ) 
        {
            return false;
        } 
        catch( InvocationTargetException e ) 
        {
            // Since we're nesting operations, let's find the root
            // exception before we continue
            final Throwable te = e.getTargetException();

            if(te instanceof FeatureOperationException)
            {
                final FeatureOperationException fe = 
(FeatureOperationException)te;

                final String feature = fe.getFeature().toString();

                ErrorDialog.openError(getShell(), 
                                      rs("err.dlg.title"),
                                      rs("err.msg.feature", feature), 
                                      fe.getStatus());

                FeaturesUiPlugin.log(fe);
            }
            else if(te instanceof CoreException)
            {
                final CoreException ce = (CoreException)te;

                ErrorDialog.openError(getShell(), 
                                      rs("err.dlg.title"),
                                      rs("err.msg.project"), 
                                      ce.getStatus());

                FeaturesUiPlugin.log(ce);
            }
            else
            {
                throw new RuntimeException(e.getTargetException());
            }
        }

        return true;
    }
